#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:1
msgid "Multilingualism"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:3
msgid ""
"A step-by-step walkthrough for tagging design artefacts with a language and "
"organization, importing translated artefacts, and working with the HR-"
"capacity Dutch reference bundle. For the architectural overview, see "
"[Multilingualism]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:7
msgid "Workflow 1 — Tag an existing artefact"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:9
msgid ""
"Open the artefact in its editor (BPMN Modeler, Form Editor, or Document "
"Composer)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:10
msgid "Scroll to the footer panel below the list."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:11
msgid ""
"**Language** — pick from the dropdown: Language-agnostic (default), English, "
"Dutch, German."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:12
msgid ""
"**Organization** — type the key, or pick from the autocomplete suggestions "
"populated from existing organizations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:13
msgid ""
"Click **Save** in the canvas toolbar. The artefact is committed and the list "
"panel regroups it under the new organization header."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:20
msgid ""
"Until you click Save, the artefact stays in its old group — the list panel "
"reflects the committed state, not the in-progress draft. Type without "
"commitment."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:22
msgid ""
"If you change the shell of a multi-process bundle and click Save, the "
"shell's language and organization propagate to every linked subprocess in "
"the same atomic write — even if you only edited the shell."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:26
msgid "Workflow 2 — Filter the list panel"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:28
msgid ""
"In any list panel (Processes, Forms, Documents), use the **search box** at "
"the top for free-text matching against name, description, and identifier."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:29
msgid "Use the **language dropdown** next to the search box to narrow by tag:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:29
msgid "`All languages` — every artefact, tagged or not"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:29
msgid ""
"`Untagged` — only artefacts with no language tag (useful for finding "
"artefacts that still need tagging)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:29
msgid "A specific language — only that code"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:33
msgid ""
"The match counter shows `<matched>/<total>` so you can see how many "
"artefacts match."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:34
msgid "Click an organization header to collapse or expand the group."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:41
msgid ""
"Untagged artefacts always match the `All languages` filter — they only "
"disappear when you switch to a specific language. Use the `Untagged` option "
"to find artefacts that still need tagging."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:45
msgid "Workflow 3 — Import a translated artefact"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:47
msgid ""
"The cleanest way to add a translated sibling is to drop a properly-named "
"file into the importer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:49
msgid ""
"Save your translated file with a language suffix: `<artefact-id>.<lang>.<ext>"
"` — e.g. `capacity-claim-intake.nl.form`, `MyProcess.de.bpmn`, `decision-"
"letter.nl.document`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:50
msgid "Click the upload icon in the editor's list panel."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:51
msgid "Select the file (or multiple files at once for a whole bundle)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:52
msgid ""
"The imported artefact is automatically tagged with the inferred language. "
"Set the organization in the footer if the file doesn't already carry it."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:53
msgid "Click Save."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:55
msgid ""
"If you exported the file from LDE earlier with **Export .form** (or the "
"equivalent), the language and organization are baked into the JSON and "
"survive the round-trip — no need to re-tag."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:57
msgid "The order of precedence for inferring the language on import is:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:59
msgid ""
"Language inside the file (`ronl:language` for BPMN, top-level `language` for "
"form/document JSON)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:60
msgid "Filename suffix `.<lang>.<ext>`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:61
msgid "Untagged"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:65
msgid "Workflow 4 — Translate an existing artefact in place"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:67
msgid ""
"When you have an existing artefact and want to produce a translated sibling:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:69
msgid ""
"**For forms:** Click **Export .form** on the original. Open the downloaded "
"JSON in a code editor, translate the user-visible text (labels, "
"descriptions, button text, option labels) keeping `id` and `key` fields "
"stable. Save with a language-suffixed filename. Re-import."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:70
msgid ""
"**For BPMN:** Export the BPMN, copy to a sibling file in your repo with "
"`.<lang>.bpmn` suffix, translate `name` attributes (process, tasks, "
"gateways, flows). Keep `id` values, `conditionExpression` values, `formRef` "
"(suffix with `-<lang>` if you want a separate Dutch form sibling), and "
"`decisionRef` unchanged. Re-import."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:71
msgid ""
"**For documents:** Documents authored in the LDE Document Composer can also "
"be exported and re-imported the same way; structural fields (zone IDs, "
"binding placeholders) stay stable across translations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:73
msgid ""
"The principle: **user-visible strings translate, code-level identifiers do "
"not**. DMN variable keys, BPMN flow IDs, form field keys, and document "
"binding placeholders all stay in their original (English) form. Only labels, "
"descriptions, headings, and button text change."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:77
msgid "Workflow 5 — Deploy a multi-language bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:79
msgid "If you've built a Dutch sibling of a process and want to deploy it:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:81
msgid "Open the Dutch BPMN in the BPMN Modeler."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:82
msgid ""
"Click **Deploy**. The deploy modal lists the resources it will deploy (shell "
"BPMN, subprocesses, forms, documents)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:83
msgid ""
"**Check for the amber language-mismatch warning.** If you see it, the bundle "
"is mixing languages — typically because one of the linked forms or documents "
"is still pointing at an English sibling. The warning lists the offending "
"codes (e.g. `en, nl`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:84
msgid ""
"Resolve the mismatch: open the misaligned form/document and either retag it "
"or replace it with the Dutch sibling. Save and reopen the deploy modal — the "
"warning should be gone."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:85
msgid "Click **Deploy** in the modal."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:87
msgid ""
"The warning is advisory, not blocking — you can deploy through it for "
"testing. For production, fix the mismatch first."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:96
msgid "Workflow 6 — Explore the HR-capacity Dutch bundle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:98
msgid ""
"A reference bundle ships with v1.6.0 to demonstrate end-to-end "
"multilingualism."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:100
msgid ""
"Open the BPMN Modeler. Find **Beheer capaciteitsclaim — proces (Voorbeeld, "
"NL)** under the FLEVOLAND group, marked with both `EXAMPLE` and Dutch "
"language."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:101
msgid ""
"Open it. The canvas shows the translated process: tasks like *Overleggen en "
"classificeren*, *Formatieclaim opstellen*, *Directiebesluit*, gateway labels "
"like *Type aanvraag?* and flow labels like *formatie* / *inhuur* / "
"*akkoord* / *afgewezen*."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:102
msgid ""
"Open one of its linked forms (e.g. *HR — Overleggen en classificeren "
"(Voorbeeld, NL)*). Every label, description, and option label is in Dutch."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:103
msgid ""
"Now open the **CapacityClaimRouting** DMN. Note that the variable keys "
"(`requestType`, `department`, `decisionRoute`, `advisoryGroup`) are still "
"English. The same DMN serves both the English and Dutch sibling BPMNs — this "
"is what stable English DMN keys buy you."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:105
msgid ""
"The bundle is the canonical example of how to do this for your own "
"translations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:109
msgid "Common situations"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:111
msgid ""
"**I tagged a form with a language and the list didn't update.** Check that "
"you clicked Save in the canvas toolbar. Until then, the change is in the "
"draft only — the list shows the committed state."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:113
msgid ""
"**The amber language-mismatch warning won't go away.** Open each artefact "
"listed in the deploy modal in turn and check its language tag in the footer. "
"The mismatch is usually a form whose tag was left at the wrong value."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:115
msgid ""
"**I imported a `.nl.form` and the language wasn't picked up.** Confirm the "
"filename ends `.nl.form` exactly (lowercase). Suffixes like `.NL.form` or "
"`.nl.FORM` won't trigger the inference."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:117
msgid ""
"**Switching to a different artefact prompts about unsaved changes I didn't "
"make.** This used to happen on document load before v1.6.0 due to a TipTap "
"mount-time event. If you see it on the current version, treat it as a real "
"bug and report it."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cmultilingualism.md:119
msgid ""
"**The footer panel for forms is missing the RoPA and DSO sections.** That's "
"expected — only BPMN processes have RoPA and DSO context. Forms and "
"documents only carry language and organization."
msgstr ""

